# Instructions for contributing

**You should give your pull request a descriptive title. Please read [Adding to this list](#adding-to-this-list).**


## Adding to this list

Please make sure your pull request follows these rules:

- Before submitting, make sure the item you are adding is relevant to the **Transformer-based segmentation**.
- Look over past recommendations before submitting your own, since they could already exist.
- Create a separate pull request for every recommendation.
- Adopt the format: Paper Name(Link) -Conference Name and Year -[github](link)
- The pull request and commit should have a useful title.
- The body of your commit message should contain a link to the repository.

Thank you for your suggestions!
